  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 4.76,
      "text": "This is a Libervox recording. All Libervox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.6,
      "end": 9.52,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit Libervox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 10.84,
      "end": 13.1,
      "text": "ASOP's fables, the Fox and the Goat.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 14.38,
      "end": 17.3,
      "text": "A fox fell into a well and was unable to get out again.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.82,
      "end": 23.24,
      "text": "By and by, a thirsty goat came by and seeing the fox in the well asked him if the water was good.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 24.04,
      "end": 28.56,
      "text": "Good, said the fox. It's the best water I ever tasted in all my life.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 29.08,
      "end": 30.34,
      "text": "Come down and try it yourself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 32.28,
      "end": 36.4,
      "text": "The goat thought of nothing but the prospect of quenching his thirst and jumped in at once.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 37.06,
      "end": 42.72,
      "text": "When he had had enough to drink, he looked about, like the fox, for some way of getting out, but could find none.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 43.86,
      "end": 46.46,
      "text": "Presently, the fox said, I have an idea.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 47.32,
      "end": 51.54,
      "text": "You stand on your hind legs and plant your forelegs firmly against the side of the well.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 51.54,
      "end": 57.14,
      "text": "And then I'll climb onto your back, and from there, by stepping on your horns, I can get out.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 57.8,
      "end": 60.06,
      "text": "And when I'm out, I'll help you out too.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 60.92,
      "end": 66.16,
      "text": "The goat did as he was requested, and the fox climbed onto his back and so out of the well.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 66.86,
      "end": 72.98,
      "text": "And then he coolly walked away. The goat called loudly after him and reminded him of his promise to help him out.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 73.78,
      "end": 79.2,
      "text": "But the fox merely turned and said, if you had as much sense in your head as you have hair in your beard,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 79.2,
      "end": 83.28,
      "text": "you wouldn't have got into the well without making certain that you could get out again.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 84.18,
      "end": 88.0,
      "text": "Look before you leap. And of the fox and the goat.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
